Definition: to enlarge beyond bounds or the truth
Example: tended to romanticize and exaggerate this `gracious Old South' imagery
Synonyms: noun, communication, overstatement, understate, exaggerate, exaggeration, act, overdraw, hyperbolize, hyperbole, hyperbolise, magnify, magnification, amplify, misinform, to, enlarge, beyond, bounds, or, the, truth, tended, romanticize, and, this, gracious, Old, South, imagery
